org.osmdroid.views.overlay

Class ClickableIconOverlay<DataType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.osmdroid.views.overlay.Overlay
      • org.osmdroid.views.overlay.IconOverlay
        • org.osmdroid.views.overlay.ClickableIconOverlay<DataType>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OverlayConstants

    public abstract class ClickableIconOverlay<DataType>
extends IconOverlay
    ClickableIconOverlay is a clickable icon item on the MapView containing IGeoPoint, unique id and data. Inspired by Marker but without the dependency to certain content and a popup-window Created by k3b on 17.07.2015.

      • onSingleTapConfirmed

        public boolean onSingleTapConfirmed(MotionEvent event,
                                    MapView mapView)
        Description copied from class: Overlay
        By default does nothing (return false). If you handled the Event, return true , otherwise return false. If you returned true none of the following Overlays or the underlying MapView has the chance to handle this event.
        Overrides:
        onSingleTapConfirmed in class Overlay
        Returns:
        true: tap handeled. No following overlay/map should handle the event. false: tap not handeled. A following overlay/map should handle the event.
